    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-08">
                        <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>15. The President appreciates most sincerely the interest expressed by the
                    Spanish Government in the promotion of peace in Europe through mediation, and
                    the confidence implied in the suggestions made; but from the information which
                    he has, the President does not believe that the time has come when a renewal of
                    the offer of mediation would be acceptable to the belligerent nations. And he
                    does not feel that it would be wise to attempt at this time, to determine the
                    conditions under which the offer of mediation should be made, when the time for
                    it arrives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
